## 6. Data Model (Core Tables)

> Note: Names are suggestions. Use UUID primary keys where indicated.

### 6.1 `users`
- `id` (UUID, PK)
- `email` (unique, required)
- `password_hash`
- `name`
- `type` enum: `human` | `integration`
- `status` enum: `active` | `platform_suspended` (optional)
- `email_verified_at` nullable (later)

### 6.2 `tenants`
- `id` (UUID, PK)
- `type` enum: `business` | `ca_firm`
- `name`
- `status` enum: `active` | `suspended` | `pending_verification`
- `created_by_user_id` (FK → users)
- `owner_user_id` (FK → users) (optional convenience)

### 6.3 `tenant_user` (membership pivot)
- `id` (UUID, PK)
- `tenant_id` (FK → tenants, UUID)
- `user_id` (FK → users, UUID)
- `status` enum: `active` | `suspended` | `invited` | `pending` | `removed`
- `member_type` enum: `internal` | `external`
- `source_tenant_id` nullable UUID (for external members; CA firm tenant id)
- `role_name` string (mirrors Spatie role in this tenant)
- `invited_by_user_id` nullable
- `joined_at` nullable

**Constraints**
- Unique (`tenant_id`, `user_id`)

### 6.4 `tenant_client_relationships`
- `id` (UUID, PK)
- `ca_tenant_id` (FK → tenants)
- `business_tenant_id` (FK → tenants)
- `status` enum: `pending` | `active` | `rejected` | `terminated`
- `requested_by_user_id` (FK → users)
- `approved_by_user_id` nullable (FK → users)
- timestamps

**Constraints**
- Unique (`ca_tenant_id`, `business_tenant_id`)

### 6.5 `ca_business_staff_assignments`
- `id` (UUID, PK)
- `relationship_id` (FK → tenant_client_relationships)
- `ca_user_id` (FK → users)
- `business_tenant_id` (FK → tenants) (denormalized)
- `created_by_user_id` (FK → users) (CA admin)
- `status` enum: `active` | `revoked`
- timestamps

**Constraints**
- Unique (`relationship_id`, `ca_user_id`)

### 6.6 `invitations`
- `id` (UUID, PK)
- `tenant_id` (FK → tenants)
- `email` (required)
- `role_name`
- `invited_by_user_id`
- `token_hash` (store hash only)
- `expires_at`
- `accepted_at` nullable
- `status` enum: `pending` | `accepted` | `expired` | `revoked`

### 6.7 `personal_access_tokens` (Sanctum)
- Default Sanctum table plus optional metadata:
  - `name` (device label)
  - `abilities` (scopes)
  - `last_used_at`
  - `ip_last_used`, `user_agent_last_used`, `device_platform`, `app_version` (optional)

### 6.8 `audit_events` (append-only)
- `id` (UUID, PK)
- `occurred_at`
- `tenant_id` nullable
- `actor_user_id` nullable
- `actor_type` enum: `human` | `integration` | `system`
- `impersonator_user_id` nullable
- `event_type` string
- `ip`, `user_agent`
- `metadata` JSON

