## 7. Authentication Flows

### 7.1 Web SPA (Sanctum SPA cookies + CSRF)
- `GET /sanctum/csrf-cookie` (or equivalent bootstrapping)
- `POST /api/auth/login`
- Auth cookie is set; SPA uses cookie automatically.
- All state-changing requests require CSRF header.

### 7.2 Mobile (Sanctum PAT)
- `POST /api/auth/mobile/login` returns bearer token (shown once).
- Flutter stores token in secure storage (Keychain/Keystore).
- Device sessions:
  - list sessions/tokens
  - revoke per token or revoke all

### 7.3 Invitations (Magic link)
- Admin invites by email
- Invitee clicks link
- If user does not exist: create user + set password
- Accept invitation -> membership activates

---

## 8. Tenant Switching & Access

### 8.1 Endpoints
- `GET /api/me`
- `GET /api/me/tenants` (list memberships)
- Tenant-scoped endpoints live under:
  - `/api/tenants/{tenantId}/...`

### 8.2 Membership enforcement
A request to `/api/tenants/{tenantId}/...` requires:
- authenticated user
- membership exists in `tenant_user`
- membership `status = active`

External members are treated identically for access checks, but have:
- `member_type=external`
- `source_tenant_id=<ca_firm_tenant_uuid>`

---

## 9. RBAC Model (Spatie Teams)

### 9.1 Team scoping
- Spatie team_id = tenant_id
- Roles are tenant-scoped
- Permissions are global strings

### 9.2 One role per membership
When setting a user’s role in a tenant:
1. remove any existing roles for that user in that team
2. assign exactly one role
3. update `tenant_user.role_name`

### 9.3 Custom roles
- Business tenant: Owner/Admin can create roles
- CA tenant: Owner/Admin can create roles
- Permission catalog remains consistent; roles are groupings

