## 12. CA↔Business Linking Workflow (Detailed)

### 12.1 Steps
1. CA tenant initiates link request -> relationship `pending`
2. Business tenant Owner approves -> relationship `active`
3. CA OwnerPartner selects staff per business client:
   - create `ca_business_staff_assignments` rows
   - ensure those CA users are members of business tenant with:
     - `member_type=external`
     - `source_tenant_id = ca_tenant_id`
     - role `ExternalAccountant` by default

### 12.2 Business controls
- Business Owner/Admin can:
  - view external members
  - suspend/remove external members
- Only Business Owner can:
  - approve link
  - terminate link

---

## 13. Integrations (Tally example)

### 13.1 Integration credential creation
Tenant Admin/Owner:
1. Creates "Tally Sync" integration
2. System creates integration user:
   - `users.type = integration`
3. Adds membership to tenant with role:
   - `IntegrationTallySync` (custom/preset integration role)
4. Issues PAT token
5. Displays token once

### 13.2 Suggested Integration role: `IntegrationTallySync`
**Permissions (example)**
- `invoices.view`
- `invoices.create` *(if Tally pushes documents)*
- `reports.view` *(optional)*

> Keep integrations least-privilege and scoped to one tenant.

