### 19.2 Authentication — Implemented

**Web SPA (cookie-based)**
- Login / register / logout via `AuthController`
- Register flow: user picks role (`owner` or `ca`) + tenant name → tenant created, user assigned as owner
- Tenant type set from role: `ca` → `ca_firm`, `owner` → `business`
- Audit events logged: `auth.login.success`, `auth.logout`, `tenant.created`

**Mobile (Sanctum PAT)**
- `POST /api/mobile/login` — returns bearer token (shown once)
- `GET /api/mobile/me` — authenticated user + tenants
- `POST /api/mobile/logout` — revokes current token
- `GET /api/mobile/tokens` — list device sessions
- `DELETE /api/mobile/tokens/{id}` — revoke specific token
- `DELETE /api/mobile/tokens` — revoke all tokens
- Login throttled (`throttle:10,1`)
- Audit events logged: `auth.login.failure`, `auth.token.created`, `auth.token.revoked`

**Invitations (magic link)**
- Send invite → `token_hash` stored, raw token emailed
- Accept: creates user if new, attaches to tenant with role, logs `member.invite.accepted`
- Decline / revoke supported
- Status field tracks lifecycle (`pending` → `accepted` / `revoked`)

### 19.3 Tenant Context — Implemented

- URL prefix: `/t/{tenant}/...` (model-bound)
- `EnsureBelongsToTenant` middleware — verifies active membership, tracks `last_tenant_id`
- `TenantPermission` middleware — checks `hasPermissionInTenant()` with per-tenant override support
- `BelongsToTenant` trait — global scope on `Client` and `Vendor` models
- Tenant switcher in nav (all user tenants loaded via `HandleInertiaRequests`)

